<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900913-0064</DOCNO><DOCID>900913-0064.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- General Motors Corp.:   GM Opens Engine Facility   Under '87 Labor Contract</HL><DATE>09/13/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A6</SO><CO>   GM LABOR</CO><IN>AUTOMOBILES (AUT)</IN><LP>   General Motors Corp. said its engine division will providejobs to about 135 laid-off hourly workers at a new engineremanufacturing business to be located in Lansing, Mich.   The venture, while small, has symbolic importance ascontract talks between GM and the United Auto Workers unionhead toward a strike deadline tomorrow night. The UAW isdemanding that GM step up efforts to re-employ idled workersby launching ventures such as this.</LP><TEXT>   The engine remanufacturing business is the first ventureto be funded by a $100 million fund established under the1987 UAW-GM national contract. The fund is designed toprovide new jobs that aren't included in the scope of GM'soperations, the auto maker said. GM officials wouldn'tdisclose the cost of the business.   The remanufactured engines will be sold through the GMservice parts operations, a GM spokesman said.</TEXT></DOC>